[src:mediatr-dotnet-lib/command-pattern] If all user actions in a program are implemented as command objects, the program can keep a stack of the most recently executed commands.
[src:mediatr-dotnet-lib/command-pattern] It is possible to send whole command objects across the network to be executed on the other machines, for example player actions in computer games.
